    "<div class=\"alert alert-info\">\n",
    "<ul>\n",
    "    <b>What is VQE?</b>\n",
    "    \n",
    "<li>VQE, Variational Quantum Eigensolver, uses variational method to approximate ground state of Hamiltonian.</li> \n",
    "    <br>\n",
    "    <b>Applications</b>\n",
    "    \n",
    "<li>Chemistry and material science : Finding the ground state and energy given Hamiltonian</li>\n",
    "<li>Optimization problem : Finding the optimal solution of the problem encoded as a Hamiltonian</li>   \n",
    "</ul>\n",
    "</div>"
   ]

    "###  Ex 1. Estimate the ground state of one qubit system and its energy for the given Hamiltonian, $H=2X$."
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "id": "korean-riding",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "#### Exact Answer"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 3,
   "id": "6892a2c3",
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [
    {
     "name": "stdout",
     "output_type": "stream",
     "text": [
      "The ground state energy of H : -2.0\n",
      "The ground state of H : [-0.707  0.707]\n"
     ]
    }
   ],
   "source": [
    "sX = np.array([[0, 1],[1, 0]])\n",
    "H = 2*sX\n",
    "eigvals, eigvecs = la.eigh(H)\n",
    "\n",
    "print('The ground state energy of H : {}'.format(np.round(eigvals[0], 3)))\n",
    "print('The ground state of H : {}'.format(np.round(eigvecs[:, 0], 3)))"
   ]

  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "id": "ebe2ff37",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "#### Using VQE "
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "id": "b1d753ea",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "**Step 1. Ansatz - State Preparation**"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "id": "0ad99c47",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "Choice of ansatz"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 4,
   "id": "51a2ea59",
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "Xop, Yop, Zop = X.to_matrix(), Y.to_matrix(), Z.to_matrix()\n",
    "\n",
    "def state_to_bloch(state_vec):\n",
    "    phi = st.data\n",
    "    bx = phi.conjugate() @ Xop @ phi\n",
    "    by = phi.conjugate() @ Yop @ phi\n",
    "    bz = phi.conjugate() @ Zop @ phi\n",
    "    return [bx, by, bz]"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 5,
   "id": "aafd7b2e",
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [
    {
     "name": "stdout",
     "output_type": "stream",
     "text": [
      "   ┌───┐┌──────┐┌───┐\n",
      "q: ┤ H ├┤ P(θ) ├┤ H ├\n",
      "   └───┘└──────┘└───┘\n"
     ]
    },
    {
     "data": {
      "image/png": "",
      "text/plain": [
       "<Figure size 432x288 with 1 Axes>"
      ]
     },
     "metadata": {},
     "output_type": "display_data"
    }
   ],
   "source": [
    "theta = Parameter('θ')\n",
    "angs = np.linspace(0, 2*np.pi, 150)\n",
    "\n",
    "qc = QuantumCircuit(1)\n",
    "qc.h(0)\n",
    "qc.p(theta, 0)\n",
    "qc.h(0)\n",
    "print(qc)\n",
    "\n",
    "st_all = [Statevector.from_instruction(qc.assign_parameters([ang])) for ang in angs]\n",
    "\n",
    "fig = plt.figure()\n",
    "ax = fig.add_subplot(1, 1, 1, projection='3d')\n",
    "b = Bloch(axes=ax)\n",
    "b.point_color = ['tab:blue']\n",
    "b.point_marker = ['o']\n",
    "b.point_size =[2]\n",
    "\n",
    "for st in st_all:\n",
    "    v = state_to_bloch(st)\n",
    "    b.add_points(v)\n",
    "    \n",
    "b.show()"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "id": "3db8e728",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "Reference: [Parametrized Quantum Circuits](https://learn.qiskit.org/course/machine-learning/parameterized-quantum-circuits#parameterized-1-0)"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 6,
   "id": "44e107e1",
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [
    {
     "name": "stdout",
     "output_type": "stream",
     "text": [
      "   ┌───┐┌───────┐\n",
      "q: ┤ H ├┤ Rz(θ) ├\n",
      "   └───┘└───────┘\n",
      "   ┌───┐┌───────┐┌───────┐\n",
      "q: ┤ H ├┤ Rz(θ) ├┤ Rx(Φ) ├\n",
      "   └───┘└───────┘└───────┘\n"
     ]
    },
    {
     "data": {
      "image/png": "",
      "text/plain": [
       "<Figure size 576x288 with 2 Axes>"
      ]
     },
     "metadata": {},
     "output_type": "display_data"
    }
   ],
   "source": [
    "# First, we need to define the circuits:\n",
    "theta_param = Parameter('θ')\n",
    "phi_param = Parameter('Φ')\n",
    "\n",
    "# Circuit A\n",
    "qc_A = QuantumCircuit(1)\n",
    "qc_A.h(0)\n",
    "qc_A.rz(theta_param, 0)\n",
    "\n",
    "# Circuit B\n",
    "qc_B = QuantumCircuit(1)\n",
    "qc_B.h(0)\n",
    "qc_B.rz(theta_param, 0)\n",
    "qc_B.rx(phi_param, 0)\n",
    "\n",
    "print(qc_A)\n",
    "print(qc_B)\n",
    "\n",
    "# Next we uniformly sample the parameter space for the two parameters theta and phi\n",
    "np.random.seed(0)\n",
    "num_param = 1000\n",
    "theta = [2*np.pi*np.random.uniform() for i in range(num_param)]\n",
    "phi = [2*np.pi*np.random.uniform() for i in range(num_param)]\n",
    "\n",
    "# Then we take the parameter value lists, build the state vectors corresponding\n",
    "# to each circuit, and plot them on the Bloch sphere:\n",
    "from qiskit.visualization.bloch import Bloch\n",
    "from qiskit.quantum_info import Statevector\n",
    "\n",
    "def state_to_bloch(state_vec):\n",
    "    # Converts state vectors to points on the Bloch sphere\n",
    "    phi = np.angle(state_vec.data[1])-np.angle(state_vec.data[0])\n",
    "    theta = 2*np.arccos(np.abs(state_vec.data[0]))\n",
    "    return [np.sin(theta)*np.cos(phi),np.sin(theta)*np.sin(phi),np.cos(theta)]\n",
    "\n",
    "# Bloch sphere plot formatting\n",
    "width, height = plt.figaspect(1/2)\n",
    "fig=plt.figure(figsize=(width, height))\n",
    "ax1, ax2 = fig.add_subplot(1, 2, 1, projection='3d'), fig.add_subplot(1, 2, 2, projection='3d')\n",
    "b1,b2 = Bloch(axes=ax1), Bloch(axes=ax2)\n",
    "b1.point_color, b2.point_color = ['tab:blue'],['tab:blue']\n",
    "b1.point_marker, b2.point_marker= ['o'],['o']\n",
    "b1.point_size, b2.point_size=[2],[2]\n",
    "\n",
    "# Calculate state vectors for circuit A and circuit B for each set of sampled parameters\n",
    "# and add to their respective Bloch sphere\n",
    "for i in range(num_param):    \n",
    "    state_1=Statevector.from_instruction(qc_A.bind_parameters({theta_param:theta[i]}))\n",
    "    state_2=Statevector.from_instruction(qc_B.bind_parameters({theta_param:theta[i], phi_param:phi[i]}))\n",
    "    b1.add_points(state_to_bloch(state_1))\n",
    "    b2.add_points(state_to_bloch(state_2))\n",
    "\n",
    "b1.show()\n",
    "b2.show()"
   ]
  },

  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "id": "ideal-instruction",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "**Step 2. Build quantum circuits to estimate the expectation value of the hamiltonian, $\\langle H\\rangle = \\langle X\\rangle$**."
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "id": "cae4cea4",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "The expectation value of an operator, $O$, with respect to a state $|\\psi\\rangle$, can be calculated as follows. \n",
    "\n",
    "$\\langle O\\rangle = \\Sigma_{i=1}^{n}λ_{i}|\\langle e_{i}|\\psi\\rangle|^{2}, ~~~ $where $O = \\Sigma_{i=1}^{n}λ_{i}|e_{i}\\rangle$.\n",
    "\n",
    "The value $|\\langle e_{i}|\\psi\\rangle|^{2}$ can be obtained by measuring a quantum circuit producing $|\\psi\\rangle$ in the eigenbasis of $O$. The appropriate post rotation gates are applied to measure a circuit in the eigenbasis of $O$ as measurement is possible only in the computational basis on IBM Quantum systems."
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 8,
   "id": "inclusive-crash",
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [
    {
     "data": {
      "image/png": "",
      "text/plain": [
       "<Figure size 417.879x144.48 with 1 Axes>"
      ]
     },
     "execution_count": 8,
     "metadata": {},
     "output_type": "execute_result"
    }
   ],
   "source": [
    "## Circuits\n",
    "\n",
    "meas_x = QuantumCircuit(1)\n",
    "meas_x.h(0)\n",
    "\n",
    "qc_x = ansatz.compose(meas_x)\n",
    "qc_x.measure_all()\n",
    "qc_x.draw('mpl')"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "id": "homeless-lobby",

   "source": [
    "**Step 3. Optimization**"
   ]

   "cell_type": "code",

    "def cost(param_vals):\n",
    "    \n",
    "    bc_x = qc_x.assign_parameters(param_vals) \n",
    "    counts = backend.run(bc_x, shots=100000).result().get_counts()\n",
    "    vals_x = sampled_expectation_value(counts, 'Z') \n",
    "    cost = 2*vals_x\n",
    "    cost_all.append(cost)\n",
    "    \n",
    "    return cost    "
   ]

   "id": "removable-zoning",

   "source": [
    "sX, sY, sZ = np.array([[0, 1],[1, 0]]), np.array([[0, -1j],[1j, 0]]), np.array([[1, 0], [0, -1]])\n",
    "H = sZ + 2*sX + sY\n",
    "eigvals, eigvecs = la.eigh(H)\n",
    "\n",
    "print('The ground state energy of H : {}'.format(np.round(eigvals[0], 3)))\n",

    "**Step 2. Build quantum circuits to estimate the expectation value of the hamiltonian, $\\langle H\\rangle = 2\\langle X\\rangle + \\langle Y\\rangle + \\langle Z\\rangle$**.\n",

   "id": "a5c77683",

    "## Circuits\n",
    "\n",
    "# for <X>\n",
    "meas_x = QuantumCircuit(1)\n",
    "meas_x.h(0)\n",
    "\n",
    "# for <Y>\n",
    "meas_y = QuantumCircuit(1)\n",
    "meas_y.sdg(0)\n",
    "meas_y.h(0)\n",
    "\n",
    "# for <Z>\n",
    "meas_z = QuantumCircuit(1)\n",
    "\n",
    "# all circuits\n",
    "qc_x = ansatz.compose(meas_x)\n",
    "qc_y = ansatz.compose(meas_y)\n",
    "qc_z = ansatz.compose(meas_z)\n",
    "\n",
    "qc_all = [qc_x, qc_y, qc_z]\n",
    "\n",
    "for qc in qc_all:\n",
    "    qc.measure_all()"

    "def cost(param_vals):\n",
    "    \n",
    "    bc_all = [qc.assign_parameters(param_vals) for qc in qc_all]\n",
    "    counts_all = backend.run(bc_all, shots=100000).result().get_counts()\n",
